21/03/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul has cancelled a planned trip to the United States later this week due to health problems, according to a statement released in Ankara on Monday (20 March). It said Gul was hospitalised and underwent successful surgery following his return from a trip to Tunisia at the weekend. According to an aide, Gul has been battling a serious respiratory infection for nearly ten days. (NTV - 21/03/06; TurkishPress.com - 20/03/06) 
